280 grams Tofu
1 sachet(s) Teriyaki Sauce
1 unit(s) Chilli
120 grams Bulgur Wheat
2 sachet(s) Apple Cider Vinegar
1 sachet(s) Sesame Seeds
1 sachet(s) Soy Sauce
1 sachet(s) Garlic, Ginger & Lemongrass Paste
1 unit(s) Cucumber
125 grams Radish
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Oil
to taste Sugar
to taste Water

Trim and thinly slice the radish.
Pop into a small bowl along with 1 tsp sugar, ¼ tsp salt (double both for 4p) and half the apple cider vinegar.
Mix together and set aside.
Stir frequently.

Trim the cucumber then halve lengthways. Bash each half with the bottom of a pot or pan. Thinly slice widthways.
In a separate bowl, toss the smashed cucumber with the soy sauce, remaining apple cider vinegar and 1 tsp sugar (double for 4p).
Set aside, ensuring to stir occasionally.

Place a pot over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Add the lemongrass paste and cook until fragrant, 30 secs.
Pour in 240ml salted water (double for 4p) and bring to the boil.
Stir in the bulgur, bring back to the boil and simmer for 1 min.
Pop a lid on the pot and remove from the heat. Leave aside for 12-15 mins or until ready to serve.
TIP: If you’re in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Place a pan over medium heat (without oil).
Once hot, dry-fry the sesame seeds until lightly toasted, stirring regularly, 2-3 mins.
Remove from the pan and set aside.
Drain the tofu and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with kitchen paper.
Halve the chilli and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

Return the pan to high heat with a good glug of oil.
Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, 6-8 mins. Shift frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.
Remove the pan from the heat and drain off any excess oil.
Stir in the teriyaki sauce and chilli (use less if you don't like spice).
Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce. Taste and season with salt and pepper, if required.

Fluff up the bulgur with a fork and divide between bowls.
Drain the pickling liquids from the radish and cucumber.
Arrange the teriyaki tofu, cucumber and radish on top of the bulgur.
Finish with a sprinkling of the toasted sesame seeds.